message.content:
<OUTPUT_TEXT>Dear Parents and Guardians,

I hope this message finds you well. As we begin the new school year, I would like to take this opportunity to remind you of the importance of adhering to the administration policies and rules governing our students. These guidelines have been put in place to ensure the safety, well-being, and academic success of all our students.

It is crucial that students arrive at school on time each day, ready to learn. Tardiness not only disrupts the learning environment but also sets a negative precedent for punctuality. Additionally, please ensure that your child comes to school dressed appropriately and follows the dress code outlined in the student handbook.

Furthermore, it is imperative that students demonstrate respect for their teachers, peers, and school staff at all times. Disruptive behavior, bullying, or any form of disrespect will not be tolerated and may result in disciplinary action.

By working together to uphold these policies and rules, we can create a positive and productive learning environment for all students. Thank you for your cooperation and support in this matter.

Sincerely,

[Your Name]
Senior Elementary School Teacher</OUTPUT_TEXT>
